different references.

361
00:28:51,454 --> 00:28:54,787
- Four of'em are about you.
- What? Give me that.

362
00:28:54,890 --> 00:28:57,950
- This is getting us nowhere.
- Let me see.

363
00:28:59,695 --> 00:29:02,596
Oh, that's not fair. I didn't even
have a soul when I did that.

364
00:29:02,698 --> 00:29:05,565
There has to be a way
to narrow down the search.

365
00:29:05,668 --> 00:29:08,967
<i>Reaper. Cross-reference</i>
<i>with the word "Reaper."</i>

366
00:29:09,071 --> 00:29:12,768
<i>- Where'd you pull that?</i>
- Came to me in the shower.

367
00:29:12,875 --> 00:29:15,969
<i>Here it is. Matthias Pavayne,</i>
<i>dark soul number 182.</i>

368
00:29:17,279 --> 00:29:20,646
- Pavayne.
- Well, there's not much here.

369
00:29:20,749 --> 00:29:23,877
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>European aristocrat, 18th century.</i>

370
00:29:23,986 --> 00:29:26,546
<i>He was a doctor</i>
<i>nicknamed "The Reaper"...</i>

371
00:29:26,655 --> 00:29:28,850
"for performing unnecessary
surgery on his patients."

372
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:31,859
- What kind of surgery?
<i>- [Wesley] The kind you don't recover from.</i>

373
00:29:31,961 --> 00:29:35,158
There's a file on him
in internal archives, classified histories.

374
00:29:35,264 --> 00:29:37,391
- He worked for Wolfram and Hart?
<i>- Not exactly.</i>

375
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:40,594
"Word spread of
his unorthodox practices.

376
00:29:40,703 --> 00:29:43,934
"Fled to California, still under
Spanish rule at the time.

377
00:29:44,039 --> 00:29:48,567
"His arrival coincided with a rash
of brutal ritualistic murders.

378
00:29:48,677 --> 00:29:53,546
Pieces of the victims
placed in a manner suggesting
an intimate knowledge of the dark arts."

379
00:29:53,649 --> 00:29:55,810
Pieces?

380
00:29:55,918 --> 00:29:58,910
