441
00:33:43,212 --> 00:33:46,613
- [Wesley] That's never good.
- What? Oh, no.

442
00:33:46,715 --> 00:33:50,082
L-I just ran out of white board.
I'm not crazy.

443
00:33:50,185 --> 00:33:52,449
- Again.
- Just scary smart.

444
00:33:52,554 --> 00:33:54,249
<i>You really think this'll bring Spike back?</i>

445
00:33:54,356 --> 00:33:56,517
Well, I had to extrapolate
a new variation...

446
00:33:56,625 --> 00:34:00,425
on interdimensional plasma dynamics
on the fly, but if the math holds...

447
00:34:00,529 --> 00:34:05,125
All right. First we'll try to get Spike back,
and then we'll deal with Pavayne.

448
00:34:05,234 --> 00:34:09,295
Wait. For this to work, it's gonna
require a massive surge of dark energy...

449
00:34:09,405 --> 00:34:11,566
- to catalyze the process.
- How massive?

450
00:34:11,673 --> 00:34:14,073
[Sighs]
The equivalent of nuclear evil.

451
00:34:14,176 --> 00:34:16,007
Where the hell are
we supposed to find that?

452
00:34:16,111 --> 00:34:19,740
Well, there is a legend...

453
00:34:19,848 --> 00:34:24,785
that tells of a volcano deep in
the forbidden jungles of South Africa.

454
00:34:24,887 --> 00:34:28,015
Or I might know a place
a little closer to home.

455
00:34:29,591 --> 00:34:31,616
The White Room?

456
00:34:31,727 --> 00:34:33,957
Why do you think they call it that?

457
00:34:34,062 --> 00:34:36,496
And how are we still in the building
when we're standing in a place...

458
00:34:36,598 --> 00:34:39,658
- that technically doesn't exist?
<i>- So this is your brainstorm?</i>

459
00:34:39,768 --> 00:34:42,760
You want to try and snip off a piece of the
conduit that connects Wolfram and Hart...

460
00:34:42,871 --> 00:34:45,533
<i>- to the other dimensions.</i>
- "Want" may be a hair strong.

461
00:34:45,641 --> 00:34:49,270
Last conduit took the form
of that creepy little girl.

462
00:34:49,378 --> 00:34:51,972
No telling what the new one's
decided to look like.

463
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:55,447
- Actually, it's not that bad.
<i>- [Big Cat Roaring]</i>

464
00:34:55,551 --> 00:34:58,611
<i>- [Growling]</i>
- If you like cats.

465
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:02,053
- Kind of a dog person.
<i>- [Roaring]</i>

466
00:35:02,157 --> 00:35:04,819
Lx-nay on the og-day.

467
00:35:04,927 --> 00:35:07,828
<i>Uh, look, we're-we're not here</i>
<i>to ruffle anything.</i>

468
00:35:07,930 --> 00:35:12,458
We're just wondering if maybe
we could borrow a couple of whiskers.

469
00:35:12,568 --> 00:35:15,162
<i>[Growling]</i>

470
00:35:15,270 --> 00:35:19,070
Whoa. Hey, easy.
It's me, Charles Gunn.

471
00:35:20,509 --> 00:35:23,342
You know I wouldn't be here
if the situation wasn't heavy.

472
00:35:23,445 --> 00:35:27,745
Just asking for a little help.
Me to you. Personal favor.

473
00:35:27,850 --> 00:35:30,717
- What do you say?
<i>- [Growling Softly]</i>

474
00:35:35,757 --> 00:35:38,988
Yeah.

475
00:35:39,094 --> 00:35:40,994
Who's a good kitty?

476
00:35:44,132 --> 00:35:46,862
<i>[Pavayne]</i>
<i>Disappointing.</i>

477
00:35:46,969 --> 00:35:50,996
<i>I expected more</i>
<i>from the soul of a vampire.</i>

478
00:35:53,509 --> 00:35:58,173
Too much conscience perhaps,
weighing it down.

479
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,407
<i>[Clanging]</i>

480
00:36:00,516 --> 00:36:04,008
<i>[Pavayne]</i>
<i>Look. Hell knows you're ready.</i>

481
00:36:04,119 --> 00:36:07,350
<i>Plump and ripe.</i>

482
00:36:07,456 --> 00:36:10,550
Beginning to understand,
aren't you?

483
00:36:10,659 --> 00:36:14,060
<i>The soul that blesses you...</i>

484
00:36:16,732 --> 00:36:20,691
<i>damns you to suffer forever.</i>

485
00:36:23,972 --> 00:36:28,932
- [Gasps]
- You go now, William, so I can stay.

486
00:36:35,951 --> 00:36:41,082
Yes, squirm, boy.
It won't make a difference.

487
00:36:41,189 --> 00:36:43,089
Getting what you deserve.

488
00:36:43,191 --> 00:36:45,421
<i>[Spike Grunting]</i>

489
00:36:45,527 --> 00:36:48,724
You're right.
[Panting]

490
00:36:48,830 --> 00:36:50,991
I do deserve to go to hell.

491
00:36:54,369 --> 00:36:57,133
But not today.

492
00:36:57,239 --> 00:37:00,003
You dare!

493
00:37:01,510 --> 00:37:05,378
Quite a bit, mate.
Reality bends to desire.

494
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:09,917
That was it, right? That's why I could
touch Fred. Write your name in the glass.

495
00:37:10,018 --> 00:37:12,782
All I had to do
was want it bad enough.

496
00:37:17,259 --> 00:37:20,854
And guess what I want to do now,
you prissy son of a bitch?

497
00:37:22,798 --> 00:37:25,323
Cute little racket you've
got carved out for yourself.

498
00:37:25,434 --> 00:37:27,925
<i>Prying off spirits</i>
<i>and sucking 'em down the chute.</i>

499
00:37:28,036 --> 00:37:31,437
<i>Kept your own toasties</i>
<i>out of the fire, didn't it? Till now.</i>

500
00:37:52,661 --> 00:37:55,391
Not so much fun
when we hit back, is it?

501
00:37:58,166 --> 00:37:59,963
It's starting to be.

502
00:38:01,570 --> 00:38:05,007
Make sure it's calibrated
to minus.058.

503
00:38:05,007 --> 00:38:06,133
Make sure it's calibrated
to minus.058.

504
00:38:06,241 --> 00:38:09,642
- Did you get it?
- Make it count. Told me we ain't gettin' any more.

505
00:38:09,745 --> 00:38:11,679
<i>It talks?</i>
<i>I didn't hear it talk.</i>

506
00:38:11,780 --> 00:38:14,806
- Maybe you weren't listening right.
- I think we're almost ready.

507
00:38:14,916 --> 00:38:16,975
- So how do we let Spike know?
- Won't have to.

508
00:38:17,085 --> 00:38:19,849
<i>This baby puts out enough juice</i>
<i>to light up Ghost City.</i>

509
00:38:19,955 --> 00:38:24,392
Anything remotely spectral around here's
about to get the tinglies.

510
00:38:25,494 --> 00:38:27,394
[Grunts]

511
00:38:30,799 --> 00:38:33,495
[Exhales]
Learned a few of my tricks.

512
00:38:33,602 --> 00:38:35,866
Means nothing, does it?

513
00:38:40,008 --> 00:38:44,342
I've cheated hell
for hundreds of years.

514
00:38:44,446 --> 00:38:48,542
Fed it other dirty little souls.

515
00:38:48,650 --> 00:38:52,711
Left me alone.
Let me get stronger.

516
00:38:52,821 --> 00:38:56,951
<i>Now, in this realm...</i>

517
00:38:57,059 --> 00:38:59,050
I am God.

518
00:38:59,161 --> 00:39:02,028
And you?

519
00:39:02,130 --> 00:39:05,361
Wood for the fire.

520
00:39:12,974 --> 00:39:17,035
This won't do.
This won't do at all.

521
00:39:17,145 --> 00:39:19,136
- [Beeping]
- [Fred] He's here!

522
00:39:19,247 --> 00:39:21,772
Spike, step
into the circle! Hurry!

523
00:39:21,883 --> 00:39:24,647
We've only got one chance
of making you corporeal again...

524
00:39:28,557 --> 00:39:30,787
Why ever would
I want to do that?

525
00:39:30,892 --> 00:39:33,122
- Fred!
<i>- Pavayne. He's killing her.</i>

526
00:39:40,035 --> 00:39:41,468
Decisions.

527
00:39:41,570 --> 00:39:46,166
The girl... [Chuckles]
Or the flesh.

528
00:39:46,274 --> 00:39:48,299
There's no time for both.

529
00:39:50,846 --> 00:39:55,078
<i>There's hope for you yet, boy.</i>

530
00:39:55,183 --> 00:39:57,276
Not really.

531
00:40:06,928 --> 00:40:09,795
No! Defilers!

532
00:40:09,898 --> 00:40:12,833
I'll cut you into nothing!

533
00:40:12,934 --> 00:40:14,663
<i>I'll feast on your brains.!</i>

534
00:40:14,770 --> 00:40:19,935
I'll swim in lakes
of your own blood!

535
00:40:20,041 --> 00:40:21,838
<i>[Angel]</i>
<i>You'll shut the hell up.</i>

536
00:40:21,943 --> 00:40:24,605
Don't kill him. If he becomes
a spirit again, we'll never stop him.

537
00:40:24,713 --> 00:40:28,171
Fine. No killing.
Just a whole lot of bruising.

538
00:40:35,157 --> 00:40:37,182
Sure you're all right?

539
00:40:37,292 --> 00:40:41,558
Yeah. It's just... you know.

540
00:40:44,366 --> 00:40:47,494
Why don't you take a break?
We'll finish up.

541
00:40:49,037 --> 00:40:51,005
Thanks.

542
00:41:11,993 --> 00:41:14,188
Don't suppose you built a spare.

543
00:41:16,431 --> 00:41:21,733
<i>Most of the pieces I used on this one</i>
<i>were practically nonexistent to start with.</i>

544
00:41:23,505 --> 00:41:27,566
Even if I could replace them,
the chances of finding another power source...

545
00:41:31,146 --> 00:41:34,138
I'm sorry.

546
00:41:34,249 --> 00:41:38,276
Don't be, luv.
Made my choice.

547
00:41:38,386 --> 00:41:41,446
Wouldn't change it for the world.

548
00:41:41,556 --> 00:41:44,684
There are other things we could try.
They're a little riskier, but...

549
00:41:44,793 --> 00:41:49,492
No. I'm not going to
end up like Pavayne.

550
00:41:49,598 --> 00:41:53,329
Cheating hell any way he could,
no matter who it hurt.

551
00:41:54,536 --> 00:41:56,800
Just proves what
I've been telling everybody.

552
00:41:56,905 --> 00:41:59,874
That I'm a handsome devil
who brightens the place up?

553
00:42:03,945 --> 00:42:05,913
That you're worth saving.

554
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:13,720
Don't have it so bad really.

555
00:42:13,822 --> 00:42:16,313
Plenty of room.
Good company.

556
00:42:18,059 --> 00:42:20,118
<i>Even picked up a few new tricks.</i>

557
00:42:30,639 --> 00:42:35,099
I guess there's worse things
than being a ghost.

558
00:42:39,514 --> 00:42:43,382
- You sure it'll hold him?
- Permanent storage.

559
00:42:43,485 --> 00:42:45,578
If there's anything
Wolfram and Hart excels at...

560
00:42:45,687 --> 00:42:48,850
it's keeping their
unmentionables unmentioned.

561
00:42:50,358 --> 00:42:54,522
Congratulations.
You get to live forever.

562
00:42:54,629 --> 00:42:56,995
Unable to move, to touch...

563
00:42:57,098 --> 00:42:59,658
<i>or to feel.</i>

564
00:42:59,768 --> 00:43:02,965
<i>Or to affect anything</i>
<i>in the world around you.</i>

565
00:43:03,071 --> 00:43:06,802
But don't worry.
I had them give you a window.

566
00:43:09,878 --> 00:43:12,870
- [Clang]
<i>- [Lock Locking]</i>

567
00:43:12,981 --> 00:43:14,949
Welcome to hell.

568
00:44:05,967 --> 00:44:08,367
Grr! Arrgh!

